{
  "texts": [
    "Image generation occurs at a resolution of 512 Â 384 pixels.",
    "The textual inversion network F h features a single Vision Transformer (ViT) layer followed by a multilayer perceptron (MLP) with three fully connected layers.",
    "It generates 16 PTEs, with training configurations including 200k training steps, a batch size of 16, a learning rate of 1 Â 10 À5 (with 500 warm-up steps), and the AdamW optimizer set with b 1 ¼ 0:9, b 2 ¼ 0:999, and weight decay of 1 Â 10 À2.",
    "The diffusion virtual try-on model is tested under predefined optimizer and scheduling strategies.",
    "Input components are randomly masked with a probability of 0.2, and the model is trained for 200k iterations using settings similar to those of the textual inversion network."
  ]
}